    {
      "id": "l6-directions",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Direction words",
      "body": "# Directions\n\nWords to find your way:\n\n- **Left** (बाएँ) and **Right** (दाएँ)\n- **Straight** (सीधे) — go ahead\n- **Near** (पास) and **Far** (दूर)\n- **Here** (यहाँ) and **There** (वहाँ)\n\nTo give a direction, English uses **turn** or **go**: *Turn left* (बाएँ मुड़ें), *Go straight* (सीधे जाएँ). The direction word comes **after** the verb."
    },
    {
      "id": "l6-ex-match-directions",
      "type": "exercise",
      "theory_ref": "l6-directions",
      "title": "Match the directions",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l6-ex-match-directions",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each English direction word with its Hindi meaning.",
        "card_ids": [
          "hi-left",
          "hi-right",
          "hi-straight",
          "hi-near"
        ],
        "pairs": [
          {
            "left": "Left",
            "right": "बाएँ"
          },
          {
            "left": "Right",
            "right": "दाएँ"
          },
          {
            "left": "Straight",
            "right": "सीधे"
          },
          {
            "left": "Near",
            "right": "पास"
          }
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
